Kendall Jenner shares her step-by-step guide to an everyday sun-kissed make-up look in Vogue India's Beauty Secrets. Of all the Kardashian-Jenner sisters, Kendall is perhaps the one with the most effortless day-to-day beauty regime. Never one to steal the credit, she shouts-out her sister and frequent collaborator Kylie, for inspiration, "When she recommends a new product, I always like to try it and see if I vibe with itâ€. The supermodel preps her skin with moisturiser and mists before applying a blend of foundation and concealer. Last but certainly not least, Kendall reaches for the hero product that makes the look: bronzer.

snippet.localized.description:

Of all the Kardashian-Jenner sisters, Kendall is perhaps the one with the most effortless day-to-day beauty regime. Never one to steal the credit, she shouts-out her sister and frequent collaborator Kylie, for inspiration, "When she recommends a new product, I always like to try it and see if I vibe with itâ€. The supermodel preps her skin with moisturiser and mists before applying a blend of foundation and concealer. Last but certainly not least, Kendall reaches for the hero product that makes the look: bronzer.

20 Amazing Facts About Disney's Most Iconic Characters:

1. Mickey was almost named Mortimer.
2. Elsa from Frozen was written as a villain.
3. Pocahontas is the first (and so far only) Disney princess to have a tattoo.
4. Aladdin has actual MC Hammer pants.
5. Dopey was supposed to be talkative.
6. Dumbo was almost on the cover of Time magazine.
7. Sulley from Monsters, Inc. is the hairiest Disney character.
8. The original Tinker Bell was played by a 71-year-old Hungarian.
9. Ursula in The Little Mermaid is based on a famous drag queen.
10. Bambi was voiced by a war hero.
11. The Beast from Beauty and the Beast is a combination of seven different animals.
12. Maui in Moana was almost bald.
13. Rex the dinosaur from Toy Story was created by the same guy who gave the world Buffy the Vampire Slayer.
14. The Genie from Aladdin had a lot of lines you never heard.
15. The voices behind Mickey and Minnie were married in real life.
16. EVE, Wall-E's female robot friend, was created by the same guy who designed the iPod.
17. The Little Mermaid's Ariel is related to Hercules.
18. Marlon Brando and the Beatles were almost Disney characters.
19. Mary Poppins' most popular song wouldn't exist with the polio vaccine.
20. Woody from Toy Story was almost a ventriloquist dummy and a bad guy!
